  },
  "sections": [
    {
      "section_id": "doc_020_s01",
      "section_label": "body",
      "section_ordinal": 1,
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p01",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 1,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p01_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "Response to a SerenadeNovember 10, 1864",
              "word_offset_start": 0,
              "word_offset_end": 6,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p02",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 2,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p02_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "It has long been a grave question whether any government, not too strong for the liberties of its people, can be strong enough to maintain its own existence, in great emergencies.",
              "word_offset_start": 6,
              "word_offset_end": 37,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p03",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 3,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p03_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "On this point the present rebellion brought our republic to a severe test; and a presidential election occurring in regular course during the rebellion added not a little to the strain.",
              "word_offset_start": 37,
              "word_offset_end": 68,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p03_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "If the loyal people, united, were put to the utmost of their strength by the rebellion, must they not fail when divided, and partially paralized, by a political war among themselves?",
              "word_offset_start": 68,
              "word_offset_end": 99,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p04",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 4,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p04_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "But the election was a necessity.",
              "word_offset_start": 99,
              "word_offset_end": 105,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p05",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 5,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "We can not have free government without elections; and if the rebellion could force us to forego, or postpone a national election, it might fairly claim to have already conquered and ruined us.",
              "word_offset_start": 105,
              "word_offset_end": 138,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "The strife of the election is but human-nature practically applied to the facts of the case.",
              "word_offset_start": 138,
              "word_offset_end": 154,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "What has occurred in this case, must ever recur in similar cases.",
              "word_offset_start": 154,
              "word_offset_end": 166,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s04",
              "sentence_ordinal": 4,
              "text": "Human-nature will not change.",
              "word_offset_start": 166,
              "word_offset_end": 170,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s05",
              "sentence_ordinal": 5,
              "text": "In any future great national trial, compared with the men of this, we shall have as weak, and as strong; as silly and as wise; as bad and good.",
              "word_offset_start": 170,
              "word_offset_end": 199,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p05_s06",
              "sentence_ordinal": 6,
              "text": "Let us, therefore, study the incidents of this, as philosophy to learn wisdom from, and none of them as wrongs to be revenged.",
              "word_offset_start": 199,
              "word_offset_end": 222,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p06",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 6,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "But the election, along with its incidental, and undesirable strife, has done good too.",
              "word_offset_start": 222,
              "word_offset_end": 236,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "It has demonstrated that a people's government can sustain a national election, in the midst of a great civil war.",
              "word_offset_start": 236,
              "word_offset_end": 256,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "Until now it has not been known to the world that this was a possibility.",
              "word_offset_start": 256,
              "word_offset_end": 271,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s04",
              "sentence_ordinal": 4,
              "text": "It shows also how sound, and how strong we still are.",
              "word_offset_start": 271,
              "word_offset_end": 282,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s05",
              "sentence_ordinal": 5,
              "text": "It shows that, even among candidates of the same party, he who is most devoted to the Union, and most opposed to treason, can receive most of the people's votes.",
              "word_offset_start": 282,
              "word_offset_end": 312,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s06",
              "sentence_ordinal": 6,
              "text": "It shows also, to the extent yet known, that we have more men now, than we had when the war began.",
              "word_offset_start": 312,
              "word_offset_end": 333,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p06_s07",
              "sentence_ordinal": 7,
              "text": "Gold is good in its place; but living, brave, patriotic men, are better than gold.",
              "word_offset_start": 333,
              "word_offset_end": 348,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p07",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 7,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p07_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "But the rebellion continues; and now that the election is over, may not all, having a common interest, re-unite in a common effort, to save our common country?",
              "word_offset_start": 348,
              "word_offset_end": 376,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p07_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "For my own part I have striven, and shall strive to avoid placing any obstacle in the way.",
              "word_offset_start": 376,
              "word_offset_end": 394,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p07_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "So long as I have been here I have not willingly planted a thorn in any man's bosom.",
              "word_offset_start": 394,
              "word_offset_end": 412,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p08",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 8,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p08_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "While I am deeply sensible to the high compliment of a re-election; and duly grateful, as I trust, to Almighty God for having directed my countrymen to a right conclusion, as I think, for their own good, it adds nothing to my satisfaction that any other man may be disappointed or pained by the result.",
              "word_offset_start": 412,
              "word_offset_end": 467,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p09",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 9,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p09_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "May I ask those who have not differed with me, to join with me, in this same spirit towards those who have?",
              "word_offset_start": 467,
              "word_offset_end": 489,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s01_p10",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 10,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s01_p10_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "And now, let me close by asking three hearty cheers for our brave soldiers and seamen and their gallant and skilful commanders.",
              "word_offset_start": 489,
              "word_offset_end": 511,
              "authorship_note": null,
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "section_id": "doc_020_s02",
      "section_label": "annotation",
      "section_ordinal": 2,
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s02_p01",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 1,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p01_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "[1]   AD, NDry.",
              "word_offset_start": 511,
              "word_offset_end": 514,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p01_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "Concerning this speech and Lincoln's response to a serenade on November 8 (supra), John Hay's Diary records under date of November 11: ``The speeches of the President at the two last serenades are very highly spoken of.",
              "word_offset_start": 514,
              "word_offset_end": 551,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p01_s03",
              "sentence_ordinal": 3,
              "text": "The first I wrote after the fact to prevent the `loyal Pennsylvanians' getting a swing at it themselves.",
              "word_offset_start": 551,
              "word_offset_end": 569,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p01_s04",
              "sentence_ordinal": 4,
              "text": "The second one, last night, the President himself",
              "word_offset_start": 569,
              "word_offset_end": 577,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "paragraph_id": "doc_020_s02_p02",
          "paragraph_ordinal": 2,
          "sentences": [
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p02_s01",
              "sentence_ordinal": 1,
              "text": "wrote late in the evening and read it from the window.",
              "word_offset_start": 577,
              "word_offset_end": 588,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            },
            {
              "sentence_id": "doc_020_s02_p02_s02",
              "sentence_ordinal": 2,
              "text": "`Not very graceful,' he said, `but I am growing old enough not to care much for the manner of doing things.'''",
              "word_offset_start": 588,
              "word_offset_end": 609,
              "authorship_note": "editorial_apparatus",
              "metaphor_instances": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
